The paper deals with sentiment classification, which is a common task in natural language processing (NLP) and falls under the category of computational linguistics (cs.CL). The paper also discusses semi-supervised learning, which is a popular technique in machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The use of feature embeddings and distance minimization techniques suggests a possible connection to information retrieval (cs.IR). Finally, the paper's focus on sentiment analysis could also be relevant to computer vision (cs.CV) applications, such as analyzing emotions in images or videos.
